 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Identity Access Administrator iRhythm Technologies 55 reviews Houston, TX iRhythm Technologies 55 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company About iRhythm: 
iRhythm is a leading digital healthcare company focused on the way cardiac arrhythmias are clinically diagnosed by combining our wearable bio sensing technology with powerful cloud-based data analytics and Artificial Intelligence capabilities. Our goal is to be the leading provider of ambulatory ECG monitoring for patients at risk for arrhythmias. iRhythm's continuous ambulatory monitoring has already put over 2 million patients and their doctors on a shorter path to what they both need â€“ answers.
 
 About this role: 
The Identity Access Management Technician's role is to plan, organize, and manage the enterprise identity environment at iRhythm Technologies. This position will ensure that the identity systems, privileged access, and associated integrations are properly planned, installed, configured, documented, secured, and maintained particularly Active Directory and Okta. This role will also be working closely with engineers and systems owners and partner with other organizations in the business. Must have excellent customer service written and verbal skills, be process driven, detailed oriented, able to adapt to change, and must be able to lead projects, such as account provisioning and de-provisioning, end user provisioning, integrating new software technology.
 
 Duties in this role include : 
Responsible for securing and documenting approvals prior to provisioning identity access
 
Responsible for securing and documenting access requirements and provisioning access for onboarding new hires
 
Responsible for de-provisioning access for offboarding employees and staff
 
Responsible for the architecting, management, support, documentation, and maintenance of documentation for identity access systems and Okta
 
Responsible for managing and maintaining data integrity and consistency within Active Directory and other Enterprise Systems
 
Adhere to industry best practices for identity technologies
 
Responsible for the provisioning of cloud based applications
 
Assist with coordinating the build-out of IAM connectors to requested applications or systems
 
Provides expert-level technical support for identity and access management systems to IDAM, other technical staff, divisions and departments, and vendors
 
Participates with the team to complete acceptance, integration testing and processes for new identity access demands
 
Participates with the team to research, evaluate, and recommend software products for identity and access management
 
Conduct internal process checks and audits
 
Participate in User Access Reviews
 
 About you: 
Bachelor's Degree in Business Management, Information Technology, Computer Science, or related field preferred
 
Must have at least 4-7 years experience in Identity and Access Management/Access Control or related position
 
Excellent interaction and communication skills; ability to communicate (both written and verbal) clearly and concisely
 
High energy and ability to work independently in a very fast growth environment
 
Experience with Microsoft collaboration suite (Office 365 Mail, Teams, SharePoint, OneDrive)
 
Extensive knowledge and hands-on experience with Microsoft Server operating Systems & Active Directory
 
Candidate should have a solid understanding of information security policies, standards, and industry leading practices
 
Self-starter; adaptable to change; motivated to set personal and program goals and proactively track performance against goals and initiatives
 
Willingness to learn new technology, tools and create new processes to meet control objectives
 
Experience working with internal and external audtiors
 
Demonstrate an understanding of SOX, GDPR, HIPPA guidelines
 
Experience with Okta or Okta Professional Certification a plus
 
Experience with AD Manager / AD Audit a plus
 
Experience and understanding of COBIT a plus
 
ISACA or ITGI Certification a plus
 
 What's in it for you: 
This is a full-time position with competitive compensation package, excellent benefits including medical, dental and vision insurance (all of which start on your first day), paid holidays, and PTO!
 
iRhythm also provides additional benefits including 401K (with company match), an Employee Stock Purchase Plan, paid parental leave, pet insurance discount, Cultural Committee/Charity events, and so much more!
 
 FLSA Status:  Exempt
 
As a part of our core values, we ensure a diverse and inclusive workforce. We welcome and celebrate people of all backgrounds, experiences, skills and perspectives. iRhythm Technologies, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer (M/F/V/D). Pursuant to San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment all qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.
 
